<body><div class=WordSection1>
<div class="brand">📚 ENGLISH CODING · 영어코딩</div>
<h1>☃️ M003 Extension — English Worksheet (Beginner)</h1>
<p><strong>Topic:</strong> Pixel-Art Snow Golem (x, y) · <strong>Course:</strong> 3D Coordinates · <strong>Level:</strong> Extension (Beginner, after Week 3) · <strong>Time:</strong> about 30 minutes</p>
<p>A bonus picture challenge: build a <strong>snow golem</strong> on your wall using <strong>(x, y)</strong> — x is <strong>across</strong>, y is <strong>up</strong>. Read the picture and place each block at its (x, y).</p>
<p><strong>Build your canvas.</strong> Run this to make a blank <strong>15 × 15</strong> wall, then put a <strong>red block at your feet</strong> as your <strong>home spot</strong>:</p>
<div style="display:flex; gap:14px; align-items:flex-start; margin:10px 0; page-break-inside:avoid; break-inside:avoid"><div style="flex:1; min-width:0"><p style="margin:0 0 4px; font-weight:700">🧩 Blocks</p><img src="../assets/week3-canvas-blocks.png" alt="MakeCode blocks: on chat command run, fill with white concrete from ~1 ~1 ~0 to ~15 ~15 ~0, replace" style="width:100%; max-width:240px; border-radius:8px; display:block"></div><div style="flex:1; min-width:0"><p style="margin:0 0 4px; font-weight:700">🐍 Python</p><pre style="margin:0; white-space:pre; font-size:12px">def on_run():
    blocks.fill(WHITE_CONCRETE,
        pos(1, 1, 0),
        pos(15, 15, 0),
        FillOperation.REPLACE)
player.on_chat("run", on_run)</pre></div></div>

<blockquote>
<p>🔴 <strong>Stand on the red block every time you run.</strong> If you move, the picture moves too.</p>
</blockquote>
<hr />
<h2>1 · Predict 🔮</h2>
<p>Read the steps. Circle your answer.</p>
<pre><code>place pumpkin block at (6, 15)
place pumpkin block at (7, 15)
place pumpkin block at (8, 15)
</code></pre>
<p><strong>A line across or up? Circle one:</strong> across · up</p>
<p><strong>Which number stays the same? Circle one:</strong> x · y</p>
<pre><code>place snow block at (4, 2)
place snow block at (4, 3)
place snow block at (4, 4)
</code></pre>
<p><strong>Across or up? Circle one:</strong> across · up</p>
<p><strong>Which number changes? Circle one:</strong> x · y</p>
<hr />
<h2>2 · Spot the Bug 🐛</h2>
<p>This code is broken. Read what it should do, then fill in the fix.</p>
<p><strong>Bug</strong> — The golem's two eyes should be at <strong>two different spots</strong>: (7, 13) and (9, 13). Both blocks land in the <strong>same spot</strong>.</p>
<pre><code>place black block at (7, 13)
place black block at (7, 13)
</code></pre>
<p><strong>Hint:</strong> the first number (x) of the second eye is wrong. One eye is further <strong>across</strong> than the other, so its x must be <strong>bigger</strong>.</p>
<p><strong>Fill the blank to fix the second line:</strong></p>
<pre><code>place black block at (7, 13)
place black block at (__, 13)
</code></pre>
<p><strong>Which number fills the blank? Circle one:</strong> 7 · 9</p>
<p><strong>Why was the code wrong? Circle one:</strong> both eyes had the same x · the color was wrong</p>
<hr />
<h2>3 · Show Your Work 📸🎥</h2>
<p>Stand on your <strong>home spot</strong> (the red block).</p>
<p><strong>Warm up first.</strong> Copy this small pumpkin head, reading each square's (x, y).</p>
